Use the standard library
This is how to odd_count of lst:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this lst's length times:
      Remember that s is item i in lst
      Remember that j is 0
      Remember that count is 0
      Do this s's length times:
         Remember that ch is item j in s
         When remainder of ch and 2 is 1, then:
            Increase count
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Add result to "the number of odd elements {count}n the str{count}ng {count} of the {count}nput."
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
